How does Prometheus collect CPU and memory metrics from a Linux server?

Good answer:

Prometheus cannot directly read server metrics. We install Node Exporter on the Linux server, which exposes system metrics through a /metrics endpoint. Prometheus is configured with the target server address and periodically scrapes those metrics. The collected data is stored as time-series data and can then be visualized in Grafana.


